/* UNION, An UNION query is used to combine the results of two or more SELECT statements into a single result set. 
 Each SELECT statement within the UNION must have the same number of columns in the result sets with similar data types. 
 NOTE:The UNION operator selects only distinct values by default. */


SELECT Product_Name ,  "In Demand" AS Demand_Status
FROM 
 superstore.superstore_sales_data
WHERE 
 Sales > 4000
UNION DISTINCT
SELECT Product_Name , "Not In Demand" AS Demand_Status
FROM 
 superstore.superstore_sales_data
WHERE 
 Sales <= 2000;
 /* This query will return a combined list of product names along with their demand status based on the sales figures.
   Products with sales greater than 4000 will be labeled as "In Demand," while those with sales less than or equal 
   to 2000 will be labeled as "Not In Demand." The UNION DISTINCT operator ensures that only unique product names
  are included in the final result set, eliminating any duplicates. */


  SELECT Product_Name ,  "In Demand" AS Demand_Status
FROM 
 superstore.superstore_sales_data
WHERE 
 Sales > 4000
UNION ALL
SELECT Product_Name , "Not In Demand" AS Demand_Status
FROM 
 superstore.superstore_sales_data
WHERE 
 Sales <= 2000;
/* This query will return a combined list of product names along with their demand status based on the sales figures.
   Products with sales greater than 4000 will be labeled as "In Demand," while those with sales less than or equal 
   to 2000 will be labeled as "Not In Demand." The UNION ALL operator includes all product names in the final result set,
   including duplicates, allowing for a comprehensive view of the demand status across all products. */